----------------------------------------------------------------
PRACTICAL 1(a): Create a Simple Sequence Based Project
----------------------------------------------------------------

AIM:
To create a simple sequence-based project in UiPath Studio that
accepts user input and displays a message using a sequence workflow.

THEORY:
A Sequence in UiPath is a linear workflow where activities are
executed one after another from top to bottom. It is the simplest
workflow type, ideal for straightforward automation tasks. Activities
like Input Dialog and Message Box are commonly used in sequences.

PRE-REQUISITES:
- UiPath Studio installed (Community Edition is free)
- Windows OS

STEPS:

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
  - Double-click the UiPath Studio icon on your desktop.
  - If not installed, go to https://www.uipath.com/start-trial and
    download the Community Edition. Sign in / create a free account.

Step 2: Create a New Project
  - On the Home screen, click "New Project".
  - Select "Process".
  - In the Name field, type: simple_sequence_based_project
  - Leave the Location as default (Documents > UiPath).
  - Click "Create".

Step 3: The Designer Opens
  - UiPath opens with a blank Main.xaml file.
  - By default, it opens in Sequence layout. You will see an empty
    canvas with a "+" (Add activity) icon.

Step 4: Add the First Activity - Input Dialog (for Hair Color)
  - In the Activities panel (left or top), search for "Input Dialog".
  - Drag and drop "Input Dialog" onto the canvas (inside the sequence).
  - In the Properties panel (right side), set:
      * Dialog Title:  "Question"
      * Input Label:   "Enter your Hair color"
      * Input Type:    Text Box
      * Value Entered: color    (this is the output variable name)
  - When you type "color" in Value Entered, UiPath will ask you to
    create a variable. Press Ctrl+K or click "Set var" and name it: color
  - Make sure the variable type is String.

Step 5: Add the Second Activity - Input Dialog (for Age)
  - Drag another "Input Dialog" activity below the first one.
  - In Properties:
      * Dialog Title:  "Question"
      * Input Label:   "Enter your age:"
      * Input Type:    Text Box
      * Value Entered: age
  - Create variable "age" as type String when prompted.

Step 6: Add the Third Activity - Message Box
  - Search for "Message Box" in the Activities panel.
  - Drag and drop it below the second Input Dialog.
  - In the Text field (Properties), type the following expression:
      "Hello, you are " + age.ToString + " years old, your hair color is " + color
  - Note: Use the Expression Editor (click the ... button next to Text)
    to type this if needed.

Step 7: Run the Project
  - Click the "Run" button (green play button) in the top toolbar,
    OR press F5.
  - A dialog box will appear asking "Enter your Hair color" — type a
    color (e.g., black) and click OK.
  - Another dialog will appear asking "Enter your age:" — type a number
    (e.g., 22) and click OK.
  - A Message Box will display:
    "Hello, you are 22 years old, your hair color is black"
  - Click OK to close.

EXPECTED OUTPUT:
  A Message Box showing:
  "Hello, you are 22 years old, your hair color is black"

